# API Testing Portfolio

This section contains API testing artifacts created using Postman for the Swagger Petstore API.

---

## Tools Used

- Postman (API testing)
- GitHub (version control and portfolio)
- REST API

---

## Project Description

The purpose of this project is to demonstrate API testing skills including:

- Sending HTTP requests (GET, POST, PUT, DELETE)
- Validating response status codes
- Verifying response body structure and data
- Working with variables in Postman
- Documenting test cases

---

## Project Structure
API-Testing
│
├── api_test_cases.md
├── api tests.postman_collection.json
└── screenshots
---

## Scope of Testing

The following API functionalities were tested:

### User API
- Create User
- Get User by Username
- Update User
- Delete User
- User Login
- User Logout

### Store API
- Place Order
- Get Order by ID
- Delete Order
- Get Inventory

---

## Test Cases

Test cases are documented in:
api_test_cases.md

They include:
- Endpoint
- Method
- Test Data
- Expected Status
- Expected Results

---

## Validation Performed

- Status code validation (200, 404, etc.)
- Response body structure validation
- Data consistency checks

---

## Notes

- Automated tests (Postman scripts) were not implemented
- Validation was performed manually
- Swagger Petstore API may return 200 status even for non-existing entities

---

## Screenshots

Examples of API requests and responses are available in the screenshots folder.

---

## How to Run

1. Import postman_collection.json into Postman
2. Set variables (e.g., username)
3. Run requests manually

---

## Conclusion

This project demonstrates basic API testing skills, including working with REST APIs, validating responses, and documenting test cases for QA purposes.
